- ability to recharge storage capacity is important as well (high transpiration rates)

Mitigate soil, aerial + H2O pollutants
- grasses were more effective at particular matter than broad-leaved or succulents, due to complex canopy structures + possessing parallel grooves on their leaes 
- root mass is important for reducint pollutant runoff

Human health and well-being
- alleviate stress + encourage physical activity
- plant-derived volatile chemicals to enhance immune functioning??
- landscape quality influences restoration potential
- phenology plays a big role
- humans have preferences for certain plant forms (flat-topped specimen)

Noise mitigation
